The paper proposes a framework for storing and managing spatial data, which involves algorithms for performing operations on raster and vector datasets. This suggests that the paper could belong to the databases (cs.DB) or data structures (cs.DS) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions algorithms for solving spatial join and retrieval problems, which are common in the computational geometry (cs.CG) and computer vision (cs.CV) fields. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of a compact data structure, which could be related to work in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) field on efficient data representation and manipulation.
